ivalent of   Alfred ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":15,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":24,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705189,"age":59,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Albreda Bisset was born in 1200, in Leicestershire, England as the daughter of John Bisset Lord, 2 husband. She married William d'Aubigny in 1212, in England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died in 1285, in her hometown, at the age of 85, and was buried in Bottesford, Leicestershire, England."},"et":{"1200–1285":"1200–1285","1194–1242":"1194–1242","1233–1301":"1233–1301","1180–1241":"1180–1241","1242":"1242","1285":"1285","1241":"1241","1194":"1194","1180":"1180","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","4 September 1242":"4. september 1242","1224":"1224","1301":"1301","1212":"1212","1200":"1200","1233":"1233","Aft 1241":"pärast 1241","Leicestershire, England":"Leicestershire, England","Bottesford, Leicestershire, E